\xb7641698aee7a193a5d5668f4148a67ba9d3e73cc980286808a737b6e5f2306b	# TODO

- AQ.Row.clone() is a mess.  You can insert a row only when it has a Row.relation.insert() method which only shows up when the row is retrieved using the `.row()` method, not the `.rows()` method.  You don't "insert" a relation so it shouldn't have an `insert()` method.  Figure out what to do here.  Also the value passed to `Relation.insert()` is not the row itself, but row.row_data or some such.
- Move `widget.js` to the widget bundle.
